     <div type="encomium">
   <pb facs="7"/>
   <head>In prayse of the Booke.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>THou O too cruell guide of louers traine,</l>
      <l>Proude in thy tyrannie on yeilded harts,</l>
      <l>When shall thy thralls forget to mourne and plaine?</l>
      <l>When wilt thou cease to hurle hatefull darts?</l>
      <l>Shall all the earth fing through her spatious parts,</l>
      <l>From out the mouth of euery fordon swayne,</l>
      <l>That thou in steed of loue, breedst hellish paine,</l>
      <l>Thou dire Vsurper of caelestiall arts.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Shall heauenlie Posie be prophaned still,</l>
      <l>In woes description to thy peeuish will,</l>
      <l>Wilt thou in steed of loue, true louers kill,</l>
      <l>Far be it from a God to doe thus ill.</l>
      <l>No PARRY no, he doth but shew thee sorrow,</l>
      <l>That from woes darknes, ioy more light may borro<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>.</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>W. M. Esq.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
